50|$|Oestreicher, {{an honorary}} doctor from the University of Sussex, fled Nazi Germany as a <b>child</b> <b>refugee.</b> He {{grew up in}} New Zealand and was for many years {{director}} of the Centre for International Reconciliation at Coventry Cathedral. Like many APF members, he also works for other peace organisations. In his case, he {{has worked for the}} Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament and was also the founding chair for Amnesty International. Though an Anglican priest, also holds a strong affinity for the Quaker religion.|$|E
