50|$|By the 1950s Toronto {{had become}} the {{epicenter}} for organizational activity among post-WWII Macedonians in North America. A total of 20,000-30,000 Aegean Macedonians, including many of the deca begalci, or <b>child</b> <b>refugees</b> of the Greek civil war, settled in Toronto. Many among them were spoiling to attack the Greek government for its poor treatment of its Macedonian minority and <b>child</b> <b>refugees.</b> The relatively liberal Canada of Prime Ministers Lester Pearson and Pierre Trudeau provided fertile ground in which a left wing emigre organization could grow.|$|R
