5000|$|Geoffrey H. Hartmann {{was born}} in Frankfurt am Main in Germany, in an Ashkenazi Jewish family. In 1939 he left Germany for England as an unaccompanied Kindertransport <b>child</b> <b>refugee,</b> sent away by his family to escape the Nazi regime. He came to the United States in 1946, where he was reunited with his mother, and later became an American citizen. Upon arrival in the US, his mother changed the family surname to [...] "Hartman" [...] to obscure its Germanic origin.|$|E
